meanings.definition: Not able to be searched or looked for.
meanings.sent1: The tiny bug crawled into an unsearchable hole in the wall.
meanings.sent2: The missing key was unsearchable in the cluttered room.
meanings.sent3: Trying to find my favorite toy in the messy room felt like a game of unsearchable hide-and-seek.
meanings.sent4: Her thoughts were like an unsearchable maze, impossible to navigate.
meanings.sent5: The treasure map led them to an unsearchable island shrouded in mist.

meanings.definition: Not able to be understood or comprehended.
meanings.sent1: The complex math problem seemed unsearchable to the students.
meanings.sent2: The ancient text written in a foreign language was unsearchable to the archaeologists.
meanings.sent3: Trying to decipher the professor's handwriting felt like an unsearchable puzzle.
meanings.sent4: Her emotions were an unsearchable ocean, deep and mysterious.
meanings.sent5: The concept of time travel remained unsearchable to the scientists.
